<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IShaderProgram.CodeFormat" Title="CodeFormat enumeration" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IShaderProgram">IShaderProgram</PageRef> ->
    CodeFormat
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>CodeFormat</TypeRef> enumeration identifies the language or binary format used by a shader code blob. Applications can query support with <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IShaderProgram.IsCodeFormatSupported">IsCodeFormatSupported</PageRef> and can query the preferred renderer format with <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IShaderProgram.PreferredCodeFormat">PreferredCodeFormat</PageRef>.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Members">
    <EnumMemberList>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="HLSL">
        Identifies HLSL source code text.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="DXBC">
        Identifies Direct3D bytecode produced by the legacy FXC compiler.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="DXIL">
        Identifies DirectX Intermediate Language bytecode produced by the DXC compiler.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="SPIRVAssembly">
        Identifies SPIR-V assembly text.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="SPIRV">
        Identifies binary SPIR-V shader code.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="GLSL">
        Identifies GLSL source code text.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="MSL">
        Identifies Metal Shading Language source code text.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
      <EnumMemberListEntry Name="AIR">
        Identifies Apple Intermediate Representation bytecode for Metal shaders.
      </EnumMemberListEntry>
    </EnumMemberList>
  </Section>
